What is JSX and how does it differ from HTML?

JSX is syntax extension of javascript that allows developers to write html like code directly into javascript files.


Difference between class and functional components?
Class components is used before the hooks and functional components used after hooks to handle state and life cycle limits
Class components is traditional approach to use it weather using hooks functional components is modern approach and easier.
Class components are extended React.component and state changes manage to use with this keyword to return jsx.
Basically, functional components are stateless but after using hooks we can maintain states


Difference between stateless and stateful ness components in react?
Stateless components are not handle state its mainly used when we dont want pefromed any operation without states.
Statefullness components are managed states based on user events or inteactions


What are PROPS in react and how are they used?
Props are basically used to transfer data between components like to from parents to child components.
Props and state are used to control and manipulate how components behave and render.


