What is Virtual DOM?
In the page we are having basically two dom's Original dom and virtual dom.
When we are updating original dom in that case all dom is getting check and update which is take times.
in virtual dom it detect which element is getting changes and particular that element is updating with original dom it saves time.

What is React lifecycle methods?
React lifecycle methods are special functions that provides granual level control to developer to hook into specific in components life cycles.
Mounting :
-constructor, getDerivedStatefromProps, render, ComponentDidMount
Updating :
- getDerivedStateFromProps,shouldComponentsUpdate,render,snapshotBeforeUpdate,componentDidUpdate
Unmounting:
-componentWillUnmount



Explain useState and useEffect hooks with examples?
useState is used to store the storedData and loading state
useEffect is used to fetched data when component is mount
/// Interval increment/decrement code

import "./styles.css";
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

const counter = () => {
  const [counter, setCounter] = useState(0);

  const increment = () => setCounter(counter + 1);
  const decrement = () => setCounter(counter - 1);

  return (
    <div className="Counter">
      <h1>Hello CodeSandboxdd {counter}</h1>
      <button onClick={increment}>Increment</button>
      <button onClick={decrement}>Decrement</button>
    </div>
  );
};
export default counter;


///Timer code
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

const timer = () => {
  const [second, setSecond] = useState(0);

  useEffect(() => {
    const interval = setInterval(() => {
      setSecond((prev) => prev + 1);
    }, 1000);
    return () => clearInterval(interval);
  }, []);

  return (
    <div class="timer">
      <h3>{second}</h3>
    </div>
  );
};
export default timer;



What is props drilling?
Props drilling is when data need to passed down from many layers of components.
eg, when one parent components is need to passed down data to great parent or nested components then in this case we need to keep passing those components also when its not needed.


What is context API?
Context api in react is features that allow us to manage component data and states at global level where all components can access from component tree, without needing to pass props manually to every level.


What is Higher order components?
Its is a function that takes components as input and return new components with additional functionality or modified behavior


What is reconciliation?
- InitialRender,state or prop change,Difing,
Update the DOM, Commit Phase

How do react portals works?
In react, portal is way to render a components children into different part of the DOM outside the parent components hierarchy, while maintaining the react component structure.


How does react router handle navigation?
It handle navigation between different views or pages without the need to reload entire page

What is React strict mode?
Helps developer to identify potential problems in an application by intentionally invoking certain warnings and behavior in the application.










